
=Description=

"The “embodied human appropriation of net primary production” or 'eHANPP accounts' allocate to any product the entire amount of the human appropriation of net primary production (HANPP) that emerges throughout its supply chain. This allows consumption-based accounts to move beyond simple area-demand approaches by taking differences in natural productivity as well as in land-use intensity into account, both across land-use types as well as across world regions."
(http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/jiec.12238/abstract)

